<subSubSection id="CD5C80FC81913F466D5C08D339F99A4D" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="07CC8899EB5099DC00B801E7A6B9F7F2" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B88D286AF9C0E57738ADB35906D100C" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">The species epithet, dynatum, is derived from the Greek work dynamis, meaning strong or powerful, alluding to the well-developed cerci of this species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F04AA19E0493E083102626F38E731FB2" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
